subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Upper part of frons (
Fig. 4
) grayish brown, middle and basal parts yellowish brown; forewings (
Fig. 5
) with black spots, veins brown; apex of pygofer (
Fig. 7
) each with an obtuse process in ventral view; basolateral fingerlike process of anal tube (
Fig. 6
) tapering at apex, apex curved dorsad, with a protrusion in lateral view; apex of aedeagus (
Figs 6, 13
) expanded in lateral view; outer process of gonostyli (
Figs 6, 10
) sharply angular at apex in lateral view.

Head and thorax.
Head (
Figs 1, 3
) significantly narrower than pronotum, without median carina. Vertex (
Figs 1, 3
) shorter in middle line than wide basally (1: 2.31), with two posterolateral areolets at base not meeting medially. Frons (
Fig. 4
) subrectangular, without median carina, longer in middle line than wide at widest portion (about 1.73: 1), lateral carinae with a row of dense sensory pits along outer margin. Postclypeus (
Fig. 4
) with distinct median and lateral carinae. Frontoclypeal suture nearly straight. Rostrum elongate, in repose well surpassing hind coxae. Pronotum (
Fig. 3
) wider than maximum width of head (including eyes) (1.32: 1), with median carina and sinuate lateral carinae. Mesonotum (
Fig. 3
) about 5.41 times longer than pronotum in midline, with distinct median carina. Forewings (
Fig. 5
) slender, longer than maximal width (2.77: 1), almost as wide at postnodal as prenodal area, veins ScP + R + MP with several sensory pits, MP3 two branched; five postnodal closed cells with C1 smaller than C2, C5 placed next to C3, C4 distally displaced after nodal line, im, r-m and anterior two-thirds of margin with white areas. Hindwings (
Fig. 8
) with lateral margin notched at CuA1, CuP, and A2, more strongly at A1; A2 not reaching posterior margin. Metatibiotarsal formula: (3+5)-6-5.

Male genitalia.
Pygofer (
Figs 6, 7
) symmetrical, gradually narrowed towards apex, with sinuate anterior and posterior margins, pygopher with internal sulcus; in ventral view, lateral margins slightly curved, apex each with an obtuse process. Anal tube (
Figs 6, 9
) in lateral view, hand-shaped, anal style slender, lateral lobes distally shorter than anal style, dorsolateral fingerlike process stout, apex rounded, basolateral fingerlike process tapering towards end, apex curved dorsad, with a protrusion; symmetrical in dorsal view, with a thick fingerlike process on each side, rounded at apex. Aedeagus (
Figs 6, 12, 13
) slender, long, apex expanded in lateral view, with tubular periandrium, lateral lobes swelling on both sides, surface beset with scale-like productions, ventral lobe slender with acute apex, dorsal lobes fingerlike; in ventral view, middle part wider. Gonostyli (
Figs 6, 7, 10, 11
) slender, divided into two parts, inner process extremely narrow, curved apically, tapering into a process; in lateral view, outer process convex, apex sharply angular, inner margin with long setae; in ventral view, divergent, top of outer process fist-like, inner process sharpened downward; in dorsal view, lateral margins curved, outer process enlarged at apex.

Remarks. This species is similar to
M. guttatus Lv & Chen, 2021
, but differs from the latter in: (1) basolateral fingerlike process of anal tube tapering at apex in lateral view (basolateral fingerlike process of anal tube rounded at apex in lateral view in
M. guttatus
); (2) apex of aedeagus expanded in lateral view (apex of aedeagus unexpanded in lateral view in
M. guttatus
); (3) outer process of gonostyli sharply angular at apex in lateral view (outer process of gonostyli nearly fan-shaped at apex in lateral view in
M. guttatus
).

Diagnosis.
Upper part of frons (
Fig. 17
) grayish yellow, middle and basal parts yellowish brown; forewings (
Fig. 18
) with black spots, veins brownish black; apex of pygofer (
Fig. 20
) each with an obtuse process in ventral view; dorsolateral and middle parts of anal tube (
Fig. 19
) each with a fingerlike process in lateral view, basolateral fingerlike process wide, apex curved dorsad; aedeagus (
Figs 19, 26
) slender and long, apex curved ventrad in lateral view; outer process of gonostyli (
Figs 19, 23
) angular at apex in lateral view.

